      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Use Cases and Examples</h2>
      <p>AI automation is being applied across a wide spectrum of legal work, delivering tangible results for firms of all sizes. In document processing, AI tools automate contract review by rapidly identifying key clauses, anomalies, and potential risks, a task that traditionally consumes countless billable hours. Some platforms can even summarize complex legal documents, creating concise overviews for quick assessment. This capability extends to e-discovery, where AI algorithms sift through millions of files to pinpoint relevant evidence, dramatically reducing review time and costs.</p>
      <p>In case management, AI is transforming workflows from reactive to proactive. Systems can now automate the creation of case chronologies, organize evidence, and even assist in deposition preparation by highlighting key documents and potential lines of questioning. For example, a mid-sized litigation firm automated its initial case assessment process, allowing it to analyze incoming client documents and identify high-priority files within minutes. This led to a 50% reduction in case preparation time and enabled the firm to take on more complex cases. Another firm specializing in corporate law used AI to automate compliance monitoring for its clients, creating automated audit trails that ensured adherence to changing regulatory requirements and significantly reduced the risk of penalties.</p>

